The highly anticipated fusion of Big Brother Mzansi and Big Brother Naija, which features 20 housemates from the two powerhouses on the continent, is finally here. The launch of the first edition of Big Brother Titans got off to a thrilling start during the dazzling live premiere in Johannesburg on Sunday. BBNaija’s Ebuka Obi-Uchendu and BBMzansi’s Lawrence Maleka will be the co-hosts for this season’s much-loved franchise. Nomsa Philiso, executive head of programming: M-Net Channels, said the viewers can expect #BBTitans to be more than just the biggest season yet. “Both Big Brother Naija and Big Brother Mzansi are massive hits in their own right and with Big Brother Titans, we are setting the entertainment bar even higher,” said Philiso. “We can’t wait to see how the housemates adapt to their new, dynamic environment, and to one another. We know [that the] viewers will find people to root for and people to root against, and we look forward to the conversations and engagement that will follow the show throughout its run.” Helmed by BBNaija’s Ebuka Obi-Uchendu and BBMzansi’s Lawrence Maleka, the glittering launch featured performances by Boohle, D’Banj, Deep London, and Bontle Modiselle and the Bontle Modiselle Dance Studio. The #BBTitans stars were introduced one by one in front of a spirited live audience before entering Biggie’s house to meet each other for the first time. The housemates are Also Read: Mzansi and Naija collide in new Big Brother Titans edition For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.